Sometimes, it'd be nice to determine if a macro is being rendered from within an existing macro.
Lets say I have:
{code}
{macro-a}
   {macro-b}
{macro-a}
{code}
What if I want {{macro-b}} to behaving differently if it is within {{macro-a}}? Right now there is no way :-(

A way of doing this is by adding a {{MacroContext}} into the {{RenderContext}}. This way I can have a look from within the {{Macro.execute()}} method:
{code}
if (renderContext.getMacroContext().getParentMacroContext() != null &&
     renderContext.getMacroContext().getParentMacroContext().getMacroName().equals("macro-a")) {
    ...
}
{code}

